##Number says outbreak 0217: new cases outside Hubei Return to zero within 4 days, Wuhan again fluctuations

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

Why do we expect daily new cases to zero by the 20th of this month? Five reasons

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The isolation ward of Caidian District People's Hospital in Wuhan, February 6,2020. Photograph: Chen Zhuo

By Xu Jin, data researcher, Caijing
Image | CAIJING visual center
Editor | Sheryl Rong

I. Trend of changes in the cumulative number of confirmed cases nationwide

As of 24:00 on February 16,70,548 cases of new coronary pneumonia had been confirmed in China. The following is a regional trend map.

Figure 1

The peak situation is obvious in the non-hubei area in China. The non-wuhan area in Hubei Province also tends to level off quickly after the data jump caused by the change of caliber.

2. NEW CASES: non-hubei areas in China continue to decline steadily, with the index day returning to zero

Figure 2

The number of new cases in non-hubei dropped to nearly 100 cases, and the number in the province was less than 4 cases. We continue to predict that the number of new cases will be zero by the 20th of this month. There are many net friends worry whether such a forecast is too optimistic, there are many net friends hope to understand the main basis for the forecast. Here's how and why:

1 We begin by continuously fitting the data on the left side of the Histogram, and we also refer to the exponential function Y R ^ x; Y

SCHEMATIC DIAGRAM 1

2 We refer to the daily distribution of new SARS cases in Beijing in 2003(see Diagram 2) , and there is no big long tail that many people worry about.

SCHEMATIC DIAGRAM 2

The proliferation model failed, especially on the right side of the peak. The emergence of the peak means that tracking, isolation, protection and other prevention and control measures in place well. The increase comes from the mother, some people think that the new cases must be related to the number of infected people, then a large scale of the mother is there, how can the increase quickly return to zero? In fact, quarantine means that the direct withdrawal of the "mother" , so that it can no longer occur could continue to occur. In the same way, tracking down close contacts is an early withdrawal of the potential "mother" . The trace is in place. The mother is almost at zero. As far as contagion is concerned, the mother is being zeroed out, and the number of New People is quickly zeroed out.

4 Many people believe that the new pneumonia is far more contagious than SARS, and the epidemic period will certainly be longer. Little did they know that there were two sides to this story, and because of the strong contagion, the outbreak became more virulent, and as a result, there was an earlier national emergency mobilization. Recall that the onset of pneumonia was roughly the same time, but by this time in 2003, the epidemic was still largely unknown, with the two sessions in Beijing in late February, the national two sessions in early March, and the first warning in Beijing in late March. And this new epidemic of pneumonia, we have now mobilized the whole nation, the prevention and control of the whole nation has crossed the daily increase in the peak value of more than 10 days.

5. There are also fears of a return to work. We can see the influx of people into the city ready, the so-called "rework tide" has been scattered. What's more, all of the rework workers come from non-hubei areas where effective tracking, isolation and screening have been achieved and are relatively safe.

Figure 3

Hubei non-wuhan region continued to decline on the basis of the decline trajectory before the adjustment of regression data. The situation is firm, showing that prevention and control measures are fully in place.

Figure 4

Wuhan data show fluctuations. For Wuhan people nervous.

3. The rate of increase of confirmed cases: The rate of increase in non-wuhan areas in Hubei Province continues to drop to 1.45% , and the rate of increase in non-hubei areas in China continues to drop to below 1% , and is expected to return to zero successively in the near future

Figure 5

Domestic non-hubei area growth rate drops to 1% , is expected to take the lead to return to zero! The rate of increase slowed to 1.45% in the non-wuhan region of Hubei Province. We can also predict the time to zero. Wuhan repeatedly.

IV. Tracking of close contacts in non-hubei areas of China: Hubei has increased, the stock continues to decline

Figure 6

Although Hubei is only a weak recovery, but it can show its close contact tracking efforts, which is a key link in the overall prevention and control system. We have been expecting this index to rise in Hubei, and today's data confirm this trend. I like it! Unfortunately, we don't have data on Wuhan yet. Domestic non-hubei area tracking efforts are still increasing.

Figure 7

Hubei is still receiving medical observation of the stock data continued to decline, indicating that the Hubei non-wuhan region of the epidemic clearly slowed down. Non-hubei areas in China continued to decline and increased.

5. The number of new suspected cases and the stock of suspected cases continue to decline

Figure 8

Hubei and domestic non-hubei area continue to both obvious decline!

Figure 9

Suspected cases stable but declining in Hubei. The non-hubei region in China is declining rapidly.

Peak number of hospitalized patients in non-hubei areas of China

10

The number of hospitalized patients in Hubei Province is still on the rise, which can be inferred from the cross-confirmation that it is mainly due to Wuhan's efforts to enhance its admission capacity. Domestic non-hubei region increased the reduction.

VII. The number of newly cured patients increased and the case fatality rate continued to rise slowly

Figure 11

Daily increase in healing non-hubei areas of the country to fall, Hubei non-wuhan areas, Wuhan rose.

12

Hubei non-wuhan area after crossing the "Golden Cross" to continue to expand the fruits of war, the daily release of more highly scarce medical resources.

13

The case fatality rate rose slowly and the general situation was normal. At the beginning of the outbreak, the daily increase in new cases may be faster than the increase in the number of deaths, resulting in a decrease in the case-fatality rate. After a period of time lag, the number of deaths increases rapidly as the disease progresses; at the same time, as the epidemic is brought under control, there is a marked decrease in the number of newly confirmed cases per day and a slowdown in the rate of cumulative confirmed cases. This fast (numerator) and slow (denominator) leads to a slow rise in the case fatality rate. It is only when the epidemic is largely over that the figure approaches the "final case fatality rate" .

Summary: The provinces outside Hubei increasingly close to zero new cases, cumulative peak. The new cases in Hubei non-wuhan area also entered the fast convergence area earlier than expected. Wuhan appears stable after the fluctuations again. That remains to be seen.
